The paper discusses the use of evolutionary techniques in robotics, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). It also mentions various disciplines that have contributed to shaping the current state of evolutionary robotics, including artificial life (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and behavior-based control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges and opportunities in the field, which could fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and systems and control (cs.SY).
